Spring Cloud config is a seperate sub project of Springboot application. There are two application. 
1) springboot config server and 
2) springboot config client


Springboot Config Server:
add dependencies: Config Server


Add Spring Actuator:

DependencyManagement: make sure springboot version is mapped properly with spring cloud version. We can check at spring cloud website

Add @EnableConfigServer
add this to enable the configuration server 



###########################################################
How to make config server reade from class path
1) add all confituration.properties file under src/main/resources/config eg. accounts.properties, accounts-dev.properties, accounts-prod.properties, cards.properties
2)application.properties 

spring.application.name = configserver
spring.profiles.active= native.     ## native for local file system where as git for github repo
spring.could.config.server.native.search-location = classpath:/config
server.port=8071


## Access properties file
<host domain name>:port/<application name>/default or /dev
eg. localhost:8080/applicationName/default
eg. localhost:8080/applicationName/dev










